Introduction

Welcome to ABC Technologies Pvt Ltd. This document outlines company policies regarding employment, leave, compensation, workplace conduct, and employee benefits. All employees are required to comply with these policies.

2. Working Hours

Standard working hours are 9:00 AM to 6:00 PM.

Employees must work 8 hours per day.

One hour lunch break is provided.

Work from home is allowed up to 2 days per week.

Flexible hours may be approved by the reporting manager.

3. Leave Policy
3.1 Casual Leave

Employees are entitled to 12 casual leaves per year.

Casual leave cannot be carried forward.

Maximum 3 casual leaves can be taken consecutively.

3.2 Sick Leave

Employees are entitled to 10 sick leaves per year.

Medical certificate required for more than 2 consecutive days.

Unused sick leaves can be carried forward up to 20 days.

3.3 Earned Leave

Employees earn 1.5 days per month.

Maximum accumulation allowed is 30 days.

Earned leave encashment is allowed at year end.

3.4 Maternity Leave

Female employees are entitled to 26 weeks of maternity leave.

3.5 Paternity Leave

Male employees are entitled to 10 days of paternity leave.

4. Holidays

Company observes 12 public holidays per year.

List of holidays is shared at beginning of year.

5. Salary & Payroll

Salaries are credited on the 30th of every month.

TDS will be deducted as per government rules.

Performance bonus is paid annually in April.

Bonus eligibility requires minimum 1 year service.

6. Probation Period

Probation period is 6 months.

Confirmation depends on performance review.

During probation, notice period is 15 days.

7. Notice Period

Confirmed employees must serve 60 days notice.

Notice buyout is allowed with management approval.

Company may waive notice period at its discretion.

8. Code of Conduct

Employees must maintain professional behavior.

Harassment is strictly prohibited.

Confidential information must not be shared.

Violation may lead to termination.

9. Remote Work Policy

Work from home allowed 2 days per week.

Remote work beyond this requires HR approval.

Employees must remain reachable during work hours.

10. Performance Appraisal

Appraisals conducted annually in March.

Promotions based on merit and performance.

Salary revision effective from April.

11. Travel Policy

Official travel must be pre-approved.

Economy class allowed for domestic travel.

Reimbursements processed within 15 working days.

12. IT & Security Policy

Company devices must be password protected.

Sharing credentials is strictly prohibited.

VPN required for remote access.

13. Overtime Policy

Overtime requires manager approval.

Compensatory off may be granted instead of pay.

14. Grievance Redressal

Complaints can be reported to HR.

Anonymous reporting is allowed.

Resolution within 10 working days.

15. Termination Policy

Employment may be terminated for misconduct.

Final settlement processed within 30 days.

16. Insurance & Benefits

Employees covered under group health insurance.

Insurance coverage up to 5 lakh rupees.

Accidental coverage included.

17. Training & Development

Employees receive 20 training hours per year.

Certification reimbursement up to ₹25,000 annually.

18. Data Protection

Personal data must comply with data protection laws.

Data misuse will result in disciplinary action.

19. Attendance Policy

Biometric attendance mandatory.

Late arrival beyond 15 minutes marked half-day after 3 occurrences.

20. Exit Policy

Exit interview mandatory.

Assets must be returned before last working day.